MEDFORD File for Multi-species Coral lncRNA Discovery and Expression

@Date 2025-09-12

@Method Long non-coding RNA (lncRNA) discovery and expression quantification from RNA-Seq libraries

@Method-Type lncRNA discovery from polyA RNA-seq

@Method-Note lncRNA discovery performed using splice-aware alignment, transcript assembly, transcript class filtering (gffcompare),
   and coding-potential assessment (CPC2), followed by quantification and differential expression analysis.

@Species Acropora pulchra

@Species-Type Fast-growing branching coral

@Species-Samples 40 libraries across 4 timepoints (same RNA-seq libraries as mRNA experiment)

@Species Porites evermanni

@Species-Type Slow-growing massive coral

@Species-Samples 38 libraries across 4 timepoints (same RNA-seq libraries as mRNA experiment)

@Species Pocillopora tuahiniensis

@Species-Type Intermediate-growth branching coral

@Species-Samples 39 libraries across 4 timepoints (same RNA-seq libraries as mRNA experiment)

@Experimental_Design Time series

@Experimental_Design-Timepoints TP1, TP2, TP3, TP4

@Experimental_Design-Note lncRNA discovery and expression based on the same time-series RNA-seq libraries used in the mRNA analysis.

@Sample_Preparation RNA extraction and library preparation as in RNA-seq experiment

@Sample_Preparation-Method Column clean-up using Zymo Miniprep

@Sample_Preparation-QC Qubit fluorescence quantification,
   1.5% TAE agarose gel electrophoresis

@Sample_Preparation-Note Libraries identical to those used for mRNA-seq; see RNA-seq MEDFORD file for details.

@Code_Ref fastp

@Code_Ref-Type Read trimming and quality filtering

@Code_Ref-Note 15bp trimmed per read (as per RNA-seq QC) prior to alignment

@Code_Ref HISAT2

@Code_Ref-Type Splice-aware alignment of RNA-seq reads to species-specific reference genomes

@Code_Ref-Note Alignment indexes generated with exon and splice-site annotations

@Code_Ref StringTie

@Code_Ref-Type Transcript assembly per sample and merged assembly across samples

@Code_Ref-Note Used to assemble candidate lncRNA transcripts from aligned reads

@Code_Ref gffcompare

@Code_Ref-Type Transcript classification relative to reference annotations

@Code_Ref-Note Candidate selection included gffcompare classes: u (intergenic), x (antisense), o (generic exonic overlap), i (intronic)

@Code_Ref CPC2

@Code_Ref-Type Coding potential assessment

@Code_Ref-Note Used to filter out putative protein-coding transcripts, retaining non-coding candidates

@Code_Ref featureCounts

@Code_Ref-Type Read summarization/quantification over lncRNA features

@Code_Ref-Note Gene-level counts for lncRNA features generated for downstream analysis

@Code_Ref DESeq2

@Code_Ref-Type Differential expression analysis of lncRNA counts across timepoints

@Code_Ref-Note R/Bioconductor package used for normalization, variance stabilization, PCA, and pairwise contrasts

@Code_Ref 31.5-Apul-lncRNA-discovery.qmd

@Code_Ref-Type Reproducible pipeline document (Acropora pulchra lncRNA discovery)

@Code_Ref-Note See D-Apul/code/31.5-Apul-lncRNA-discovery.qmd

